<font color="#FF0000">RESPONSE TO JJ</font><br>
<tt>Tue Feb 11  1:30:57 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
JJ the Boonirat<br><br>
The content of my response to you, I stand by.  The anger and hostility I cannot defend.<br><br>
You said: &gt;This is my first time to see this site. Therefore, I have no feel for what this is really all about. I admit that up front.&lt;<br>
Fantastic.  I applaude and respect honesty.  I try my best to be honest on site otherwise, my purpose for being here is defeated.  More than anything else, I admire honesty.<br><br>
You said:&gt;My first impression is that somehow a small group of people are enjoying some kind of intellectual game about Nam, Protestors, the Vets, and a series of overlapping generations.&lt;<br>
Pre-judgement I cannot tolerate.  I watched this site from the beginning, over a long period of time before I stepped in to throw my two cents in.  At no time have I degraded or diminished anything anyone had said.  You did this right off the bat.  Yes, you did mean to demean, otherwise, you wouldn't have said it.  You demeaned and diminished the hard work that I and others had put into the site.  That may not have been your intention, I'll allow for that, but, that was the effect.<br><br>
You said:&gt;Back off on this discussion some. Get back to some real issues. Unless those who talk here are into some kind of political science project, try to reach out to the real impact on Americans that the Nam was.&lt;<br>
Again, pre-judgement, plus arrogance by assuming that real work is not going on by the parties involved.  By, assuming that real issues are not involved in this process.  You diminished the hard work people had vested in this site by equating it with &quot;a political science project&quot;.<br><br>
If you look at the site from the beginning, you will see that I have tried to encourage ANYONE to join in.  I benefit from a diversity of views and opinions, and there is not one who I don't have respect for, because, it is not an easy thing to do, putting your guts on the line.  This may seem trite, but I see everyone on site as a hero, for I know what it takes and how hard it is to do it.<br><br>
My suggestion to you, if you had not done so, check out POV's introduction to see what their intent for this site was.  Then go back to the beginning of this thread and you will see that we are living up to that intended purpose.  I say this with no anger or malice, just a suggestion.<br><br>
Yes, I am sure you know me, possibly, more than you admit.  Yes, I am not unique in the way you mean.  My response, however, was, also, not unique.  I had received several e-mailings expressing, &quot;great job&quot;, from some keeping track of this site.  My response to them was the following:  It was not a &quot;great job&quot;, I had allowed myself to get angry, and I had slapped someone down.  I did not respond as appropriately as I should have, and for this I apologize.  Again, however, I stand by the content.<br><br>
Irregardless of how I feel about your initial posting, I would give my left nut, my limbs, and my life, to defend anybodies right to be here.  You are no exception.  Get what you can, give what you can.  That is what it is all about.
<p><code>-- docdel@maui.net  (Doc Del) </code><p>


